1
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:35,479
This trick of mine will definitely work.

2
00:01:35,479 --> 00:01:36,720
Do you know what my trick's

3
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:37,960
key point is?

4
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:39,960
You need a thick skin.

5
00:01:39,960 --> 00:01:41,490
And you must be persistent.

6
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,000
Persistent.

7
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,280
My bad. I'll go try again.

8
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:07,720
Jia, Yan.

9
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:10,520
Jiajia.

10
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,920
I feel like something's off with him today.

11
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,180
Really? What's wrong?

12
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,640
I don't know either.

13
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,920
It's baffling.

14
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:19,100
I feel there's definitely a problem.

15
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,680
Being overly attentive for no reason

16
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:24,010
means he's up to no good.

17
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:27,040
Something's not right.

18
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,300
Definitely not right.

19
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,240
Jiajia.

20
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:33,680
Has the time issue with low-energy orbit transfer

21
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,410
been solved?

22
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,320
There will be more mission requirements in the future,

23
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:37,960
so the low-energy transfer orbit

24
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:38,880
will be used long-term.

25
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:41,400
However, we haven't abandoned other options.

26
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,480
Hear me out, okay?

27
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,160
Okay.

28
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:44,120
For the upcoming missions,

29
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,360
I'm thinking of

30
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:47,079
having these four newcomers

31
00:02:47,079 --> 00:02:48,680
assist you in completing them.

32
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:51,079
They are young, enthusiastic, and full of ideas.

33
00:02:51,079 --> 00:02:53,480
What they lack is experience and opportunities.

34
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:56,000
You guys work hard. Don't let me down.

35
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:57,040
Rest assured.

36
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:58,760
We are already devoted and passionate,

37
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:00,280
just waiting to make our mark.

38
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,000
Don't rush.

39
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,200
Heavier tasks

40
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:05,200
will come with the arrival of the new leader.

41
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:06,560
New leader?

42
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:08,680
Who?

43
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,920
General Manager Gu from Xi'an Flight Control

44
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:13,050
has officially been transferred here

45
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,080
as the Haoyue 4 mission's

46
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,970
one of the chief designers.

47
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:18,480
He will work with us

48
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:21,140
to complete the Xingqiao Mission together.

49
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:23,880
Qin.

50
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:38,840
My name is Gu Lifeng.

51
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:40,880
Starting today,

52
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:44,210
as the chief commander of Haoyue 4,

53
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:46,840
Mr. Qin and I will lead the team together

54
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:48,810
to complete the Xingqiao Project.

55
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,260
No need to clap.

56
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,640
Come on, introduce yourselves.

57
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,680
Hello, everyone.

58
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:55,400
I am from

59
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,040
Beijing Institute of Space Technology,

60
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:59,280
associate senior engineer Zhang Ziming.

61
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:01,540
I will be working with you all from now on.

62
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,050
Nice to meet you all.

63
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,680
I am from Xi'an Flight Control,

64
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,200
the chief designer, Jiang Mengyao.

65
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,000
I'm a Scorpio,

66
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,820
and I like milk tea and hot pot.

67
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:13,360
Unlike Mr. Gu and Mr. Zhang,

68
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,620
everyone here is a stranger to me.

69
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:18,200
I hope to get to know you all soon.

70
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,200
And I hope in our future work,

71
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,769
you can take good care of me.

72
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,760
Welcome Mr. Gu, Mr. Zhang,

73
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:28,680
and Ms. Jiang to join us.

74
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:30,880
I look forward to learning from you all.

75
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:31,880
Welcome, welcome.

76
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:32,520
You brighten up the whole institute.

77
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:33,560
Well, Old Qin,

78
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:35,159
is the work going smoothly now?

79
00:04:35,159 --> 00:04:37,040
It will definitely be smoother now that you're here.

80
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:37,800
Okay, good.

81
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,100
You guys continue.

82
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,320
I heard

83
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:45,680
this Mr. Jiang

84
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:47,360
is Old Gu's top warrior.

85
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,760
He was selected directly from school back then,

86
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:52,080
and became a manager half a year earlier than Sister Jia.

87
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:52,760
Here is your milk tea.

88
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:53,360
Thank you.

89
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:56,970
Swiping now.

90
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,240
All set.

91
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,920
If you have time to worry about this,

92
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:04,240
you might as well think about how to work hard.

93
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,240
Please swipe your card.

94
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:05,760
True.

95
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:10,120
The biggest problem now is...

96
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,820
We are Old Qin's soldiers.

97
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,600
It's hard being caught between two big forces.

98
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:19,120
We'd better behave ourselves from now on.

99
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:41,570
You're all here.

100
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,480
Mr. Jiang.

101
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:45,840
Have a seat.

102
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:47,170
Thank you. Please, sit.

103
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:52,280
I saw you guys coming in from a distance.

104
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:55,800
I came from Xi'an in a hurry this time.

105
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,440
I didn't have time to bring any local specialties.

106
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,440
I prepared a small gift for each of you.

107
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:00,680
I hope you like them.

108
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:01,400
Yours.

109
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:02,280
Thank you, Mr. Jiang.

110
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:02,880
Yours.

111
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:05,840
Thank you.

112
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,200
Mr. Jiang, you're too polite.

113
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,520
We didn't prepare any gifts for you,

114
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:11,720
but you got us something.

115
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,580
How about this?

116
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:14,640
Next time you have time, you treat us to a meal.

117
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:15,120
No,

118
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:17,170
we'll treat you to a meal, okay?

119
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:20,080
There's no need to be so polite.

120
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:21,920
This is just a bookmark from the Xi'an Museum.

121
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,180
It's just a small gift.

122
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,360
You are Ying Ziqi.

123
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:33,880
Yes, I am.

124
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:36,800
My best friend is currently working on

125
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,330
Professor Qiao's project.

126
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:41,020
Professor Qiao talks about you all the time.

127
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:43,420
I've also read your master's thesis.

128
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:45,000
Your multi-window launch trajectory design

129
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,060
for the same mission is quite unique.

130
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:49,400
How about this.

131
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,000
Let's add each other on WeChat.

132
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:51,760
If we get the chance,

133
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:53,480
we can go visit Professor Qiao together.

134
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,000
Okay.

135
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:54,960
Well...

136
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:56,260
How about this?

137
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,840
I'll create a group chat

138
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,560
and invite Mr. Jiang.

139
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,520
It'll be easier for us to communicate.

140
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:04,560
How does that sound?

141
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,440
Sure.

142
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:07,140
You're always so thoughtful.

143
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,040
Cai Bo'ao.

144
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,840
I've heard you were at Flight Control.

145
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:18,280
We finally meet.

146
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,120
When I was in college,

147
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,840
I really admired Academician Cai.

148
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,370
I even audited his classes.

149
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:26,000
And your father, Professor Cai,

150
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:26,920
once went to Xi'an

151
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:28,160
to guide our work.

152
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:31,120
It's fate that we can work

153
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,250
on the same mission.

154
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,440
Tell me,

155
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,520
are they both doing well?

156
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:38,960
They're doing great.

157
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,330
That's good.

158
00:07:44,159 --> 00:07:44,760
All right.

159
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,130
I'll leave you to it.

160
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,159
Bye, Mr. Jiang.

161
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:50,620
Bye, Mr. Jiang. Take care.

162
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,760
Professor Cai.

163
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,000
Academician Cai.

164
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,480
Then may I ask which Cai you are?

165
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:17,960
I'm just a nobody.

166
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:20,280
Just Xiao Cai.

167
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,200
Can we just talk nicely?

168
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,360
Aren't we brothers?

169
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,200
Wei, I really didn't lie to you.

170
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,760
Just listen to me.

171
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:33,400
Yes.

172
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,090
My dad is Professor Cai.

173
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,000
And my grandpa is Academician Cai.

174
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,400
I am a third-generation aerospace worker.

175
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:43,960
But I really didn't ride on their coattails at all.

176
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,280
I'm not lying to you.

177
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:48,680
You don't understand my pain at all.

178
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,360
Qi.

179
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:02,240
Can you say something?

180
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:04,820
You should believe me, right?

181
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,940
I really didn't lie to you.

182
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:08,560
My mom said

183
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:10,210
that if I don't get a PhD,

184
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:11,240
I'll be the one in the Cai family

185
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,570
with the lowest degree.

186
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,920
My dad said if I don't work in aerospace,

187
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,920
I'd be wasting our aerospace genes.

188
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,760
Also, the number of times I see my grandpa

189
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:19,840
is pitifully small.

190
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,770
How am I riding on their coattails?

191
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,120
How could I?

192
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:25,120
I really didn't lie to you.

193
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:36,780
You guys don't understand my pain at all.

194
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,330
How am I riding on their coattails?

195
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,040
If I do well,

196
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,480
it's expected of me.

197
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:48,080
I'm a Cai.

198
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,480
A third-generation aerospace worker.

199
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,610
If I don't do well...

200
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,920
I just can't do poorly.

201
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:55,560
Always making me talk.

202
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:56,760
What is there to say?

203
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:00,040
You completely don't understand my pain.

204
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,240
If you had said so earlier,

205
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,640
we wouldn't have given you such a hard time.

206
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:12,530
I had no idea you had so many difficulties.

207
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:15,480
Alright.

208
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:17,760
Show Bao more love from now on.

209
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:21,040
Okay.

210
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:26,970
The first flight mission still depends on performance.

211
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,640
Let's work hard together.

212
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:29,840
We'll participate together,

213
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,120
and celebrate our success.

214
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:31,720
Great.

215
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:35,400
Then Team Muxing...

216
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:36,540
Team Muxing...

217
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:37,880
Let's go!

218
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:47,730
Don't touch my flowers.

219
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:52,600
I haven't seen you in so many years.

220
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:55,040
Ready to put on a second act here?

221
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,360
Plants have their own personalities too.

222
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,240
If you raise them like this,

223
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,520
you'll ruin them sooner or later.

224
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,720
You don't know a thing.

225
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:03,840
Look here, here.

226
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,960
Pampered and spoiled.

227
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:06,290
Do you know what this is?

228
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,040
What is it?

229
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:09,160
I designed this myself.

230
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:12,260
An automatic watering and lighting system.

231
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:15,680
I have to say, we haven't seen each other for years.

232
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:16,360
Why do I feel like

233
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,080
you're giving off

234
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:19,000
such strong old man vibes?

235
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,000
Are you going through menopause?

236
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,130
Sure, you're young.

237
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,480
On your Moments,

238
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:25,210
you always post those pretentious poems.

239
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:26,920
Those doggerels of yours make no sense.

240
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:27,840
Stop embarrassing yourself.

241
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:29,920
Why don't you write some for me to read?

242
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:31,000
Are you done?

243
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,440
- You begged the old leader
- Leave when you're done.

244
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,240
to bring me back from Xi'an.

245
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,880
You need to mind your work attitude.

246
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:37,800
Letting a little power go to your head.

247
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,760
Okay.

248
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:40,720
Then you can go.

249
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,640
All right, let's wait and see.

250
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,800
Dad, listen to me.

251
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:54,120
This is really not a misunderstanding.

252
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:56,120
We've already made it clear.

253
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:57,480
Dad.

254
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,480
Just leave my business alone.

255
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,400
Zhang Ziming,

256
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:16,720
where are you?

257
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,320
But we can imagine.

258
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:21,360
If we develop the spacecraft's

259
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:23,880
autonomous orbit measurement methods

260
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:26,600
and real-time orbit determination capabilities,

261
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,520
wouldn't it

262
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:29,720
greatly reduce the risk of the mission?

263
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:31,320
Could you

264
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,720
elaborate on this for us?

265
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:34,960
Let's just enjoy our meal today.

266
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:38,280
We will have plenty of opportunities to cooperate in the future.

267
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:39,080
Alright then.

268
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,760
These noodles are too spicy.

269
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:41,320
Are they?

270
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,280
I'm not very good with spicy food.

271
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:44,080
Zhang Ziming.

272
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:46,320
Jia.

273
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,720
You guys go ahead and eat.

274
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:48,560
This way.

275
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:56,720
Did you call my dad?

276
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,680
What right do you have to make that call?

277
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:01,940
No, is there a problem?

278
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,160
What do you think?

279
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,240
This is between the two of us.

280
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,400
Is it necessary to drag them into it?

281
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:08,800
I think it's necessary

282
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,800
to let your parents know about this.

283
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:13,220
It's also about politeness and respect.

284
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:19,680
Then have you ever respected me?

285
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,440
I don't think there's anything wrong with what I said.

286
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:23,960
I did this

287
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,420
for the sake of our future.

288
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:27,730
I hope you don't misunderstand me.

289
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,930
There's no misunderstanding.

290
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:36,120
You made your point very clear.

291
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:38,450
Let's just leave it at that.

292
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:40,000
Don't pester me anymore.

293
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:01,560
Jiajia.

294
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,880
What are you doing?

295
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:05,210
Why aren't you working?

296
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,440
I'm just cleaning up.

297
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,420
Getting familiar with the place.

298
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:14,120
Jiajia.

299
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:16,040
Just say it.

300
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,890
Are you done with your work?

301
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,800
I bought you some milk tea.

302
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:22,360
Half sugar, less ice, new flavor.

303
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:22,960
Try it.

304
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:25,840
Thanks.

305
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:32,640
Are you upset about something, Jia?

306
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:36,200
Don't worry.

307
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:36,920
There's nothing

308
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,240
a cup of milk tea can't fix.

309
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,520
If there is, then

310
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:41,920
buy two.

311
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:43,000
No, no, no.

312
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,540
You've been quite proactive lately.

313
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:47,200
That's good.

314
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,840
I'm just trying to create

315
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:51,300
a good working environment for you seniors.

316
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,580
It's the least I can do.

317
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:54,800
Jia.

318
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:57,000
Yesterday, I happened to see

319
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,930
an orbit design you made years ago.

320
00:14:59,280 --> 00:15:00,440
That's our Jia.

321
00:15:01,160 --> 00:15:02,440
It perfectly illustrates

322
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:04,360
the intellectual beauty of the women at Muxing,

323
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,360
academic beauty,

324
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:07,000
and exploratory beauty.

325
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,000
Why do I feel more and more

326
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,760
that you're up to no good?

327
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:12,160
No.

328
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,160
I'm completely sincere, Sister Jia.

329
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,760
My admiration

330
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,160
and respect for you

331
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:18,760
come straight from the bottom of my heart,

332
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:19,600
endless like a flowing river.

333
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,720
Okay, okay, okay.

334
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:22,120
Stop talking.

335
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:24,040
I'm really not used to you being like this.

336
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:25,200
It's fine, Sister Jia.

337
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,440
You'll get used to it.

338
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:27,640
I'll still need a lot of

339
00:15:27,640 --> 00:15:29,960
your help with work in the future.

340
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:31,720
Since you didn't charge me any tuition,

341
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,580
I've already gotten a great deal.

342
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:37,760
You really don't need to exaggerate so much.

343
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:38,800
As for work matters,

344
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:39,760
you can ask me anytime.

345
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:40,820
Got it, Sister Jia.

346
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:43,080
Sister Jia, Sister Jia, Sister Jia!

347
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:44,490
I suddenly remembered.

348
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:46,800
I heard you guys made an orbital plan

349
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,920
for a solar system exploration satellite before,

350
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:49,440
right?

351
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:52,010
Can I take a look?

352
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:54,560
Why the sudden interest?

353
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:56,280
Nothing.

354
00:15:56,280 --> 00:15:58,080
It's just that even though we're part of the mission,

355
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,140
we can't slack off.

356
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:00,840
I want to use it as a reference

357
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:01,840
and learn from it.

358
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:04,040
It's good that you have this intention.

359
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:04,560
But

360
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:06,080
that was just an experimental preliminary plan.

361
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:06,920
If you want to learn,

362
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:08,960
you still need to do the data calculations at hand well.

363
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:09,690
Definitely.

364
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,440
Isn't it the more, the merrier, Sister Jia?

365
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,840
Sister Jia, just let us see it.

366
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,970
Let us experience it and learn from it.

367
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:16,080
Alright, alright.

368
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:16,560
Role model.

369
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:17,520
Alright.

370
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,120
You're making yourself dizzy shaking your head like that.

371
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:22,160
This requires permission,

372
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:23,640
so I'll approve it for you.

373
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:31,200
You don't have to do this in the future.

374
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,800
It's good that you want to learn.

375
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:34,000
Just say it directly.

376
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:36,050
Understood.

377
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:39,170
Alright.

378
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:39,960
Take this ID number

379
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:42,090
and register at the computing center.

380
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:44,820
Thank you, Sister Jia.

381
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,000
Wait a minute.

382
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:48,360
Remember what I said.

383
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,680
This is not the most important thing.

384
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:50,960
Work comes first.

385
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:52,410
Definitely.

386
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,360
Jiajia, this noon...

387
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:55,360
Zhang Ziming,

388
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,440
I've said all I need to say.

389
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:57,970
Can you stop looking for me?

390
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:58,760
Jiajia.

391
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:00,900
It's like this.

392
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,800
I think regarding your parents,

393
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:05,010
you might have misunderstood.

394
00:17:05,079 --> 00:17:06,680
I don't want to pressure you.

395
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:07,730
I just think that

396
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,760
since we've been together for so long,

397
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:12,560
we should at least give our families an explanation.

398
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:14,480
I will talk to my parents myself.

399
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:16,579
Stop flattering yourself, okay?

400
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:19,440
It's been so many days.

401
00:17:19,839 --> 00:17:21,880
Can't we just talk calmly?

402
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:25,530
There's no need.

403
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:28,920
I have to work. Go back to your business.

404
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:11,240
Guys.

405
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,920
Jia gave me the access.

406
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:25,320
Bao didn't get slapped for nothing.

407
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:26,560
He did a great job.

408
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,330
I told you it would work.

409
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:29,930
Have a seat, Mr. Bao.

410
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:32,920
I saw Zhang Ziming

411
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:34,490
go look for Jia just now.

412
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:35,720
Jia's boyfriend.

413
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:36,920
That's him?

414
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:39,640
What? Any gossip?

415
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:41,200
No, no, no.

416
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:42,840
I just think

417
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,660
he is not that good.

418
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:46,580
Don't underestimate him.

419
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:48,200
He's an aerospace elite.

420
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,040
They happen to be doing a mission together this time.

421
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:53,040
The young couple fights side by side to overcome difficulties

422
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,900
and improve their relationship.

423
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:58,440
Stop gossiping and go to the computer room.

424
00:18:58,440 --> 00:18:59,120
Once we get all the data,

425
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:00,920
we can start working on the plan.

426
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:07,920
It's useful,

427
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,690
but we can't use it too much.

428
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:27,160
Nan,

429
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:28,280
great news.

430
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:29,120
Come.

431
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:30,700
Let me tell you something.

432
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:33,040
Jia

433
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:34,520
has approved our access.

434
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,120
The missing data will be filled in soon.

435
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:40,160
Now that the data is ready,

436
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:41,280
can we start designing

437
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:43,000
our plan?

438
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:46,200
Okay, I didn't expect Jia to actually approve it.

439
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,080
Of course.

440
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:49,040
Although Jia didn't say it out loud,

441
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:50,840
she was actually quite pleased.

442
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:52,840
We got her.

443
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,560
With a little trick,

444
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:57,640
the data is back in our hands.

445
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:01,160
I hope this project design

446
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:02,200
goes smoothly.

447
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:02,900
You.

448
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:05,480
Caibao,

449
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:09,780
what are you doing?

450
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:11,160
Jia.

451
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:12,920
Yan.

452
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:14,940
Where is Wu Wei?

453
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:16,680
Wei.

454
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,640
The competition was my idea.

455
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:37,640
It has nothing to do with the others.

456
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:42,760
Jia.

457
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:47,440
I really shouldn't have lied to you about the permissions.

458
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,320
I'm sorry.

459
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:53,440
But that's a separate matter.

460
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:56,360
Participation in this competition is voluntary.

461
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:58,400
We don't have any rules against it.

462
00:20:58,680 --> 00:20:59,720
Before we entered the competition,

463
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:00,880
we had already made up our minds.

464
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:02,280
We will only use our free time

465
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:03,480
to do this.

466
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:04,920
Besides,

467
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:06,320
we are participating in this competition

468
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:07,840
just to train ourselves.

469
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:10,960
There is no rule saying you can't participate in competitions.

470
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:12,120
But in our industry,

471
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:14,920
the more basic things are, the more important they are.

472
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,520
I know what you're thinking.

473
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:18,000
You just failed the flight simulation,

474
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,120
and want to regain your pride through the competition, right?

475
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:22,380
You are trying to run before you can walk.

476
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:24,840
In the end, the loss outweighs the gain.

477
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:26,300
Since I am in charge of you,

478
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:28,170
and I have promised Mr. Qin,

479
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:30,200
I must take this responsibility.

480
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,400
And let me remind you,

481
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:33,560
there's an assessment during the probation period.

482
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:34,640
You doing this now,

483
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:36,440
what are you trying to do?

484
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,980
None of you want to stay here anymore?

485
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:42,160
Mr. Li, don't completely write them off.

486
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:44,620
I think we can't blame them entirely.

487
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:47,960
It must be hard for them after failing the simulated flight.

488
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:50,690
Their intention to seize an opportunity is good.

489
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:51,980
How about this?

490
00:21:52,640 --> 00:21:54,770
Send me the orbit data you calculated.

491
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:57,540
We sent it to the intranet.

492
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:13,760
Why is there still a third of it not calculated?

493
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:15,080
We will finish it according to the schedule.

494
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:16,520
You need to understand clearly,

495
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:17,560
in this industry,

496
00:22:17,840 --> 00:22:20,120
there is no such thing as finishing according to schedule.

497
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:22,120
Will the launch window wait for you?

498
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:26,120
Aerospace is all about racing against time.

499
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:26,680
Look,

500
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:29,480
you haven't even done your own job well,

501
00:22:29,480 --> 00:22:31,600
and you still have the mind to participate in competitions.

502
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:32,730
Who taught you this?

503
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:35,040
Fine.

504
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:38,320
Since you have so much energy to spare,

505
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:39,840
starting from today,

506
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:41,920
I will assign daily tasks

507
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:44,240
to make sure your excess energy

508
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:45,380
is fully utilized.

509
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:47,800
I will check your progress every day.

510
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,290
As for the competition,

511
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:51,020
I will talk to Director Cao

512
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:52,480
and withdraw from it.

513
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:54,440
Before eight on Monday,

514
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:56,840
I'll be waiting for your first round of assignments.

515
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:57,600
Get to work.

516
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:01,040
Qu Ruonan.

517
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:11,900
I've told you everything I had to say.

518
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:13,610
You figure it out yourself.

519
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:19,840
What do we do now, guys?

520
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,640
Stop thinking about what to do.

521
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:23,320
Think about the assignment Jia mentioned

522
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:24,980
and what we should do about it.

523
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:31,160
Why are you looking at me?

524
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:33,220
Don't you always have the most ideas?

525
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:35,280
Not this time.

526
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:36,640
Didn't Sister Jia say

527
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:39,080
to finish our work properly before talking about anything else?

528
00:23:39,080 --> 00:23:40,000
Yeah.

529
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,480
With this much data,

530
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:44,840
it'd be good enough to just finish the assignment.

531
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:48,280
Doesn't Chu Jiajia just want

532
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:50,520
to force us to withdraw from the competition?

533
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:53,250
Not only will I not withdraw, I will participate.

534
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:54,960
And I will even complete the assignment she gave us

535
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:56,000
beautifully.

536
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:59,360
Give me more of the data to calculate.

537
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:00,220
I'll handle it.

538
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:02,980
Forget it, let's just distribute it evenly.

539
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:04,440
I said I'll handle it, so I'll handle it.

540
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:06,100
Whether you believe me or not.

541
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:08,120
Let's not. If we're handling it, we handle it together.

542
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:10,050
We'll all work overtime together.

543
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:13,090
It's too late. Time to get off work.

544
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:16,320
I find you really...

545
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:18,090
Didn't you say you'd handle it?

546
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:21,260
Let's go back and pull an all-nighter together.

547
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:27,560
Then let's handle it together.

548
00:24:27,560 --> 00:24:29,240
Then let's do it.

549
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:29,900
Let's do it.

550
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:32,560
Then let's all handle it.

551
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:35,080
What's so hard about that?

552
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,800
Whether we pull an all-nighter

553
00:24:37,800 --> 00:24:39,720
or not, we're staying up.

554
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,680
Let's just do it together.

555
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:52,680
It's a new day.

556
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:54,480
Go Team Muxing!

557
00:24:58,840 --> 00:24:59,600
Qi,

558
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,800
did you really stay up all night?

559
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:05,160
Look at Qi,

560
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:07,100
and then look at yourself.

561
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:13,800
Is the new cup working out for you?

562
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:22,000
Nan is asking you a question.

563
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,120
How's the new cup?

564
00:25:23,360 --> 00:25:24,920
Isn't it better than the one that broke?

565
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:26,560
I think the old one was better.

566
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:29,020
The style and color of this cup are too tacky.

567
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,660
I think it looks great.

568
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:33,240
Really.

569
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,100
Such a tacky color.

570
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:48,800
Forget it. You can't cure bad taste.

571
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:51,680
Brother.

572
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:54,000
She kindly gave you a mug.

573
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:55,740
And you're being so picky.

574
00:25:58,240 --> 00:25:59,240
Pour it yourself.

575
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:05,200
I'm not being picky.

576
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:08,160
It's ugly.

577
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:09,620
That's an objective fact.

578
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:15,440
An objective fact.

579
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:18,800
Then don't use it.

580
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:21,400
If you don't like it, throw it away.

581
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:23,600
You really bite the hand that feeds you.

582
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:26,100
No one is forcing you to use it.

583
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:37,000
Ying Ziqi, did you take the wrong medicine?

584
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:39,800
Nan kindly gave you a gift.

585
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:41,160
It's fine if you don't like it.

586
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:43,560
But you didn't have to say things to break her heart.

587
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:44,680
It's okay. Um.

588
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:48,400
I just remembered I have something to do.

589
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:50,080
I'll head back first.

590
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:52,900
Didn't you give me the mug?

591
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:55,680
Me giving you a gift? What are you thinking?

592
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,340
You're flattering yourself.

593
00:26:58,240 --> 00:26:59,160
You broke my mug.

594
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:00,620
Shouldn't you replace it?

595
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,800
Didn't you make it clear to him?

596
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:03,560
I told you.

597
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:06,880
I came back from drinking that day and gave you the cup,

598
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:08,760
and told you it was from Nan.

599
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:09,960
Right.

600
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:15,480
Then I made a mistake.

601
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:18,800
It's fine.

602
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:21,600
Everyone has different tastes.

603
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:33,000
So this cup was a gift from Nan.

604
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:34,400
This cup,

605
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:36,400
you gave it to Qi, didn't you?

606
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:41,000
I knew it. That day in the pantry,

607
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:43,120
you kept fiddling with Qi's cup.

608
00:27:46,480 --> 00:27:47,360
Qu Ruonan,

609
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:50,800
could it be that you...

610
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:51,360
Caibao.

611
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:58,980
I'm leaving first.

612
00:27:59,120 --> 00:27:59,600
I...

613
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:00,880
Are you really mad?

614
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:07,400
Go away.

615
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:09,800
Nan.

616
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:12,640
Are you really mad?

617
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:14,800
She is mad.

618
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:17,320
She is mad.

619
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:20,760
To be exact,

620
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:22,800
this should be called

621
00:28:22,800 --> 00:28:23,600
awkwardness.

622
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:29,140
Dumbfounded, huh?

623
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:32,250
It's all your fault.

624
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:35,240
Are you seriously shifting the blame to me?

625
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:36,760
When others give it, it looks good.

626
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:38,320
But when I give it, it's ugly, right?

627
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:39,280
Besides,

628
00:28:40,040 --> 00:28:42,370
isn't it an objective fact that it's ugly?

629
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:44,440
What should I do then?

630
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:47,040
Although I don't really get it.

631
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,240
But Qi,

632
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,320
according to standard procedure,

633
00:28:50,320 --> 00:28:51,880
shouldn't you hurry to catch up to her

634
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,360
to apologize and explain?

635
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:56,240
You must apologize.

636
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:57,560
Be sincere about it.

637
00:28:57,760 --> 00:29:00,690
Don't ruin the team's unity at this critical moment.

638
00:29:04,040 --> 00:29:05,920
Stop staring and go.

639
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:08,560
Run.

640
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:09,480
Keep it up.

641
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:15,160
Hello, a glass of water, please.

642
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:16,000
Okay.

643
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:19,960
What I said earlier,

644
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:23,900
I hope you didn't take it to heart.

645
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:29,960
I misunderstood.

646
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:34,600
I didn't know you gave me the cup.

647
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:35,440
It's fine.

648
00:29:35,800 --> 00:29:36,880
Like I said,

649
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:39,840
everyone's taste is different.

650
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:44,600
Hello, your water.

651
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:45,240
Thanks.

652
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:03,570
I thought Wu Wei gave me the cup.

653
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,050
He didn't make it clear.

654
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:07,840
We're used to being sharp-tongued.

655
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:08,480
So,

656
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:13,380
you're not angry, are you?

657
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,480
No, no, no.

658
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:17,000
Why would I be angry?

659
00:30:17,320 --> 00:30:18,960
What I said earlier

660
00:30:19,200 --> 00:30:20,320
was all a joke.

661
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:23,000
If there's nothing else, I'll go first.

662
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:31,160
And,

663
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:34,640
thank you for the chocolate last time.

664
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:35,440
Chocolate?

665
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:39,560
I mean, after the simulated flight control reset,

666
00:30:39,560 --> 00:30:41,020
the chocolate you gave me.

667
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:44,720
Um...

668
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:49,580
Actually, what you said that time

669
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:51,440
was quite useful.

670
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:55,740
So for this orbital competition,

671
00:30:57,640 --> 00:30:59,440
I want to participate properly.

672
00:31:02,040 --> 00:31:03,500
Let's work hard together.

673
00:31:08,120 --> 00:31:10,560
Um, you guys discuss it first today.

674
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:12,800
I'll go home and think about the algorithm.

675
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:15,240
Remember to use the water cup.

676
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:16,520
Okay.

677
00:31:24,240 --> 00:31:25,240
I'm leaving. Bye.

678
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:26,160
Bye.

679
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:28,520
Jiajia.

680
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:32,680
Wait a minute.

681
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:34,960
I found some books at home.

682
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:36,840
I don't know if they're yours,

683
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,240
so I brought them for you.

684
00:31:45,840 --> 00:31:46,480
Thank you.

685
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:51,010
I've reflected on myself these past few days.

686
00:31:51,240 --> 00:31:53,560
I shouldn't have ignored your feelings.

687
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:54,960
I apologize.

688
00:31:58,080 --> 00:32:00,210
Actually, I don't want to just give up.

689
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:02,820
Our relationship of so many years

690
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:04,520
hasn't been easy.

691
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:10,800
It really hasn't been easy all these years.

692
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:14,480
But what exactly are you thinking?

693
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:15,480
Can we talk?

694
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:25,400
I don't know what to say.

695
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:29,360
I just feel

696
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:31,170
quite regretful

697
00:32:31,880 --> 00:32:32,940
and like a failure.

698
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:38,040
At work,

699
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:39,680
I can calculate

700
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:42,040
the orbit of a satellite tens of thousands of kilometers away.

701
00:32:42,040 --> 00:32:42,680
I can overcome

702
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,810
one problem and glitch after another.

703
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:47,640
But when it comes to relationships,

704
00:32:48,120 --> 00:32:49,480
I am truly powerless.

705
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:52,960
I don't know how to describe it.

706
00:32:53,080 --> 00:32:54,340
It's just this feeling

707
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:55,860
of being powerless

708
00:32:56,760 --> 00:32:57,840
and disappointed.

709
00:33:00,440 --> 00:33:03,000
Whether it's towards myself, you,

710
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:05,600
or this relationship.

711
00:33:09,800 --> 00:33:11,260
Do you remember this book?

712
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:15,210
I remember back then...

713
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:17,040
It should be Haoyue-3.

714
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:21,840
It was our first collaboration,

715
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:25,640
and we encountered technical difficulties right from the start.

716
00:33:25,640 --> 00:33:27,120
To overcome this problem,

717
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:30,320
we stayed up day and night for months.

718
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:33,980
We constantly tested and revised our ideas.

719
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,840
At the toughest moment,

720
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:38,080
I gave this book to you.

721
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:41,770
It's my favorite sci-fi novel.

722
00:33:42,400 --> 00:33:44,520
The mission went smoothly after that.

723
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:46,320
I remember after the celebration party,

724
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:48,050
I confessed my feelings to you.

725
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:49,600
Yeah.

726
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:54,200
Everything felt so wonderful back then.

727
00:33:54,840 --> 00:33:56,960
Because we had a common goal,

728
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:58,400
a common dream.

729
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:01,410
We both loved aerospace and longed for space.

730
00:34:02,480 --> 00:34:05,360
I guess we were kindred spirits.

731
00:34:11,440 --> 00:34:14,880
But I don't know since when,

732
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:17,600
everything changed.

733
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,800
It seems like many things

734
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:22,480
were slowly worn away by reality

735
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:24,760
and disappeared.

736
00:34:28,239 --> 00:34:29,400
It's really a shame.

737
00:34:30,239 --> 00:34:32,440
I think the problem between us might be

738
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:35,199
that what I consider important,

739
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:36,480
you don't care about.

740
00:34:37,040 --> 00:34:38,840
And what we want from each other,

741
00:34:40,159 --> 00:34:41,239
we just can't give.

742
00:34:45,080 --> 00:34:47,880
So there is really no need

743
00:34:47,880 --> 00:34:49,480
to keep draining each other.

744
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:52,760
I'm sorry.

745
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:56,800
There's no need to say sorry either.

746
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:01,290
Let's just leave it at this.

747
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:03,040
Jiajia.

748
00:35:05,080 --> 00:35:06,040
Can I have this book,

749
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:07,440
"Rendezvous with Rama"?

750
00:35:09,760 --> 00:35:11,480
This book was meant for you

751
00:35:11,920 --> 00:35:13,280
if you had opened it.

752
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:25,860
Dafu, Chashao,

753
00:36:26,080 --> 00:36:27,540
how are things on your end?

754
00:36:27,640 --> 00:36:28,440
Master Ying,

755
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,920
I've uploaded the data for you.

756
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,250
I sent mine to you first.

757
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:34,040
I sent mine too.

758
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:36,280
I sent mine too, Qi.

759
00:36:54,200 --> 00:36:55,320
I think it's ready.

760
00:36:55,960 --> 00:36:56,720
Upload it.

761
00:37:00,160 --> 00:37:01,490
The scoring starts now.

762
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:03,520
The scores are updated in real time.

763
00:37:05,040 --> 00:37:06,240
What place is this?

764
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:07,080
Fifty.

765
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:20,160
Fifth place.

766
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:24,200
We are in fifth place.

767
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:26,880
Wei, Wei, fifth!

768
00:37:26,880 --> 00:37:27,600
We won.

769
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:29,160
We are in fifth place.

770
00:37:30,960 --> 00:37:32,400
I'd like to see

771
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,840
who dares to underestimate us now.

772
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:35,720
This is what they call becoming famous overnight.

773
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:36,760
Let's celebrate properly.

774
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:37,760
Celebrate!

775
00:37:43,360 --> 00:37:45,890
Our joy has turned to sorrow a bit too quickly.

776
00:37:46,720 --> 00:37:49,960
They used this satellite toolkit to optimize the data.

777
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:51,720
I've seen their plan.

778
00:37:51,840 --> 00:37:53,680
Their approach is basically the same as ours,

779
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:55,410
or perhaps ours is even better.

780
00:37:55,640 --> 00:37:56,840
But in terms of score,

781
00:37:57,480 --> 00:37:58,920
it's hard for us to surpass.

782
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:00,560
The difference between our plan and theirs

783
00:38:00,560 --> 00:38:02,440
lies in data optimization.

784
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:04,520
This toolkit is very powerful.

785
00:38:04,520 --> 00:38:05,720
Whether it has been optimized or not

786
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:07,480
makes a world of difference in the results.

787
00:38:07,480 --> 00:38:10,160
So we can't use this software?

788
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:12,640
We can't. Only they can use it.

789
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:13,880
That's not right.

790
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:15,800
I remember according to previous international conventions,

791
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:16,800
this type of software toolkit

792
00:38:16,800 --> 00:38:18,040
can be shared internationally.

793
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:19,720
The software we developed and designed

794
00:38:19,720 --> 00:38:21,040
has also been fully shared.

795
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:21,960
That's us.

796
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:23,220
They are not that kind.

797
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:24,720
They used to share it,

798
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:26,440
but after we announced the Haoyue Project,

799
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:27,700
they stopped sharing.

800
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:28,820
It's banned for us.

801
00:38:28,960 --> 00:38:29,840
All foreigners can use it,

802
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,120
only we can't.

803
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:32,880
If the data is not optimized,

804
00:38:32,880 --> 00:38:35,040
our plan is useless no matter how well it is done.

805
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:36,280
This is too much.

806
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:38,520
Is this too much?

807
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:40,640
Is this just too much?

808
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,280
This is shameless. This is despicable.

809
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:43,240
This is dirty.

810
00:38:43,240 --> 00:38:44,800
This is technological competition.

811
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:46,760
It's always been a game of catch-up.

812
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:48,040
This isn't the first time.

813
00:38:48,040 --> 00:38:50,770
We still have to prove ourselves with our skills.

814
00:38:51,560 --> 00:38:52,520
It's just data.

815
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:54,650
Can't we just calculate it ourselves?

816
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:55,560
Wei.

817
00:38:55,880 --> 00:38:58,360
Are you trying to finish it with your courage and perseverance?

818
00:38:58,360 --> 00:38:59,120
Didn't our predecessors

819
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:01,080
figure it out using an abacus?

820
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:05,240
Wei.

821
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:06,720
It's impossible for us to finish.

822
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:08,520
The amount of data is just too massive.

823
00:39:08,520 --> 00:39:09,440
With just the four of us

824
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:10,840
working day and night without rest,

825
00:39:10,840 --> 00:39:11,600
even when the competition ends,

826
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:13,400
we might not be able to finish it.

827
00:39:18,160 --> 00:39:19,440
What if we could apply for

828
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:20,720
a supercomputer?

829
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:23,000
A supercomputer?

830
00:39:23,560 --> 00:39:24,840
Don't you know the new Director Gu

831
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:26,720
spends all day in the computer center?

832
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:28,880
He's been here for days without any progress.

833
00:39:28,880 --> 00:39:30,360
If we run into him there,

834
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:32,420
wouldn't that be asking for trouble?

835
00:39:40,360 --> 00:39:41,520
Think of a way.

836
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:43,840
Think of a way.

837
00:39:44,520 --> 00:39:45,280
What for?

838
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:47,040
We're in an academic competition,

839
00:39:47,040 --> 00:39:48,520
and we have some data that

840
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:50,980
needs to be optimized by the supercomputer.

841
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:55,320
Who sent you here?

842
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:57,160
We came here ourselves.

843
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:01,880
Who is your advisor?

844
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:03,760
Qin Bojun, Mr. Qin.

845
00:40:08,200 --> 00:40:09,080
Alright.

846
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:11,040
Thank you so much.

847
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:16,240
What kind of competition requires a week's use?

848
00:40:16,240 --> 00:40:16,840
Why don't you ask me

849
00:40:16,840 --> 00:40:18,400
to lend you the computer room?

850
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:19,000
Let me tell you,

851
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,640
if you were competing to land on the far side of the moon,

852
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:22,440
I would even let you have my seat.

853
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:24,760
Stop messing around and get out of here.

854
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:25,880
Mr. Gu, please calm down.

855
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:27,880
Young people don't know any better.

856
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:30,400
Let's go.

857
00:40:30,560 --> 00:40:31,690
Sorry to bother you.

858
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:38,220
I was just looking for you.

859
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:39,680
Are you still busy?

860
00:40:40,080 --> 00:40:41,400
Go back early when you're done.

861
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:42,760
Why? Are you going to do my work for me?

862
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:43,680
Come on, you do it.

863
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:45,540
Okay, I'll help you with the work.

864
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:47,160
Why are you so good to me?

865
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:50,680
Alright, I know you care about me.

866
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:51,920
Lately,

867
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:53,720
you've been working overtime for me and stuff.

868
00:40:53,720 --> 00:40:54,600
There's only a little work left.

869
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:55,680
I'll go back when I'm done.

870
00:40:55,680 --> 00:40:56,640
Hurry back.

871
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:57,440
Okay.

872
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:07,160
Still not leaving? Want to stay with me?

873
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:11,760
Those guys from the Muxing team

874
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:13,400
have really grown some nerve.

875
00:41:13,400 --> 00:41:15,040
They don't take me seriously at all.

876
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:15,840
What's wrong?

877
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:18,120
Check the group chat.

878
00:41:18,640 --> 00:41:20,800
I didn't plan to let them participate before.

879
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:21,860
But they insisted.

880
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:25,250
Now their terrible results are embarrassing me.

881
00:41:25,400 --> 00:41:27,200
No, I have to get an explanation.

882
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:29,160
Do they still want to stay in flight control?

883
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:29,720
Jiajia.

884
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:30,680
Don't be mad.

885
00:41:30,680 --> 00:41:32,840
These kids really went too far.

886
00:41:32,840 --> 00:41:34,440
Everything can be discussed.

887
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:35,800
There's nothing to discuss.

888
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:37,600
We were too easy on them before.

889
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:39,680
Now we need to keep them in line.

890
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:43,540
Talk it over properly.

891
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:51,690
Why is everyone just standing around?

892
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:03,200
It's such a mess.

893
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:05,040
In this environment,

894
00:42:05,200 --> 00:42:06,930
how can you make anything good?

895
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:08,690
Jia, we'll clean up in a bit.

896
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:13,440
Look at your faces.

897
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:16,240
You all look like you just got out of a hard labor camp.

898
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:17,500
Don't you want to live?

899
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:19,920
People who don't know

900
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:21,480
would think we are evil landlords,

901
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:23,120
bullying you poor tenants.

902
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:26,200
The data verification is finally over.

903
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:27,760
Why don't you take a rest?

904
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:28,960
Aren't you tired?

905
00:42:29,160 --> 00:42:29,920
Don't you care about your health?

906
00:42:29,920 --> 00:42:30,520
We do.

907
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:32,040
But we are not tired.

908
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:33,040
We can keep going.

909
00:42:37,120 --> 00:42:38,000
I'm sorry, Jia.

910
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:40,680
It was my idea to enter the competition secretly.

911
00:42:40,680 --> 00:42:42,360
I submitted the proposal myself.

912
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:44,160
Actually, Jia, it was us.

913
00:42:44,160 --> 00:42:44,960
Let him speak.

914
00:42:50,200 --> 00:42:52,000
This has nothing to do with them.

915
00:42:52,160 --> 00:42:53,120
I did it all by myself.

916
00:42:53,120 --> 00:42:54,000
Just come at me.

917
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:56,520
Well done, Mr. Wu.

918
00:42:57,480 --> 00:42:58,340
Come down here.

919
00:43:00,760 --> 00:43:05,240
The names of the spacecraft and related missions in this drama have been fictionalized.

